values:
Hey kids... nother day, nother writing... I had hoped to keep up with this thing somewhat, but, no luck so far! lol 

I started a new job at Mercury Insurance two weeks ago today. It rocks my cock so hard! I love this frickin job! It's such a cake walk and the people here are really nice and the money is SOOOO much better! lol So, to celebrate my new job, I went out and bought a new car. =) I got a 2006 Scion tC. It's black and so awesome I wanna cry! I put my subwoofers in it and they're pretty nice, but, I need to buy a new head unit. The factory one just ain't cutting it at ALL! heh 
 
I haven't done much since getting back from vaca in July.... I go out sometimes and drink a lil here and there, but that's about it. Llama and I started a new bet. Neither one of us can have sex or masturbate again until we are down to 170 lbs. the conditions of the bet are that if she fails, she has to announce to the whole world that I give way better head than she does and I'm tighter, as well as pay for everything we do from now on without bitching about it. If I lose, I have to move in with her when she buys the house. 

I ain't worried about loosing one bit. lol In two weeks of working here, I'm already down 15 pounds and she's gaining. lol I take stairs all day long and I've been eating really well so far, and she hasn't.... So, we'll see. Plus, sex, not happening anyway. I'm waiting til marriage. =) 

anyways, I'll write more later. Just had some time at work because I finished my test first. Today's the last day of training and tomorrow we start on the mentoring stuff on the phones. fun fun....

Later kiddies!

Jase.

Went to bricktown 54 last night. 
So over straight clubs.
This one wasn't so bad, good atmosphere, hot guys, but again, straight club. 
I'm starting to look into a school in orlando, and may be moving there at the beginning of the year. I had a pretty big realization yesterday about the sort of thing I could see myself doing for the rest of my life and didn't know why I didn't see it before, so, now I'm looking at schools to see what's the what yo. I'm so not gonna say what it is I wanna do though, had enough ridicule this week for it. It's cool though, makes me wanna do it that much more. =) 
I'm dying for sleep. Ever since I got back from Vaca, I haven't had a good night of rest. 
Oh, and I'm bombing my room right now. And getting quotes to replace the window in my room. I'm so tired of bugs getting in through the window because the seals are completely gone and the window won't close all the way. I had a major battle with the godzilla of all cockroaches this morning. I'm getting ready for work and I'm sitting on the bed putting on my shoes, when I hear my bag rattling. *side note, This is a bag I got when I was in New York and bought some awesome clothes, so, I WANTED to keep it as a nice souvenier. Anyways, So I hear the bag rattling around and get up to check why it was doing it and it was moving all around, like noticeably. So I'm thinking my little Sh*t rat dog has gotten into my room and is messing around, so, I walk closer.... And suddenly the bag like moves across the floor and the next thing I know, I see the big godzilla cockroach stomping around on the outside of the bag now, breathing fire breath and stomping on new york bag city. I was so disgusted I started screaming and jumping around like a little girl, and ran to get the bug spray. It took me so long to find it I was afraid godzilla would be gone and be nesting somewhere in my room unseen.... but when I got back, it was just chillin there, lookin like it was gettin some sun. So, I sprayed. 
And I sprayed.
Nothing. 
So I sprayed some more. Suddenly, Godzilla turns to me and begins CHARGING at me. I just gave up and squashed it with my pretty shoes that now are in the garbage because there's icky godzilla remains all over them. 
So, the moral of the story was that now I am bug bombing my room while I'm at work because that CAN NOT happen again. Like, ew. 
Ok homeys, that's my words for the day. Peace like monkey grease.

So last night, I had a dream about Joey... and it was really odd and I can't remember a lot of it.... Somehow, we were somewhere and we ran into each other... and he was hostile as always, but we hung out anyway because we hadn't seen each other in a long time. For whatever reason, he was upset and sad, and I made him come stay at my house for the night and watch movies. At some point he started crying and I hugged him and he grabbed on so tight... and I just held him there until we fell asleep, tangled up in each other, like we always used to do. It was such a weird weird weird dream and ever since I woke up, I haven't been able stop thinking about him.... So, grrrr, I hate ex boyfriends. Maybe it's my mind playing subconscious distraction so that I don't think about today being my brother's birthday.... I dunno, but, it was one weird ass dream! Just thought I pop out an entry about it for the hell of it. =)
Later.

So Catina pointed out that I haven't written on here in a long time, so, horray for entries! heh Life is... pretty boring. I mostly work and that's about it. Sometimes I go out to Georgie's with friends, usually Tuesday night when it's not retardedly packed. But that's about it.... Tonight I'm going to a banquet for work. That should be fun.... in the not, sense. I hate these stupid work functions, but, sadly I have to go. I spent last night at Catina's watching movies and sleeping on the world' most uncomfortable futon in the world. Oh my god.... lol So yeah, that's about where I'm at. Sad, lonely, and pathetic. But finally driving the car I want. I just put $1000 into my stereo system. Yay tax return! I'm so happy! Now I can do the real work I need to do on it... Oh well, gettin gone now. Gotta go do some laundry and shit before night. Peace all!
Jay.

So I guess I'm not going to maine now.... I called Kevin last night because I hadn't heard from him in a few days, and felt like talking to him. Aparently I sounded all serious and stuff because he called back a few times to see what was wrong, but, I just wanted to talk to him. lol 
Well, this morning, he came on here and read my livejournal. My last post, I spoke about how I didn't feel the same way he did, and I was scared about going up there, and all this other stuff. So, he concluded that it would not be a good idea for me to come up there anymore... Which I kind of agree with... I know it would be a bad idea for me to come up there because one way or another, someone would get hurt and that's not fair... But I was actually starting to like the idea of trying not to worry about that and just having fun with my friend. I really wanted to go up there and spend the time with him and see him, but, Oh well now.... I don't know if he's going to read this, and I don't really care. If you do read this, just know this isn't my way of telling you what's going on. This is my way of getting my thoughts out of my head. I'm sorry if what I was thinking at the moment wasn't what you wanted to hear, but that's why it's my journal. Yeah, it's public on the internet, but not intended for use as a medium to my emotions. 
Oh well... now my thought track is gone.... I'm gonna go back to work and have the fun of telling my boss all the trial mumbo jumbo was for nothing. Maybe I'll justkeep the days off for the heck of it.... I need a vaca... heh
Jay.

Ah.... so now that my LSD hot dog fun is out of the way, I can write a post... I'm at work, again, bored senseless. All I did yesterday was sleep. And sleep. And sleep. It was quite fun.... I feel overwhelmingly rested today. 
I have to go down and go tanning today because I feel uber white... I haven't gotten to go as much as I would have liked to... 
And all this stuff with Kevin has gotten me a little more worried... I know he's hoping for something to come out of this trip, and I know nothing will... And I'm starting to wonder if I should go or not because I do not want to lead him on and hurt him.... But he keeps making me promise that I won't back out of this trip. That I won't cancel on him on his birthday. I dunno.... I don't know what I'm doing anymore.... I wish I did. Life would be so much easier if I had even the slightest idea.... Oh well... 
I gotta get back to work, so,I guess I'll write more later...
Peace out... 
Jay.

1. Take your LJ username and replace each letter with the corresponding number (A=1, B=2, etc...). A=1 E=5 B=2 a=1 b=2 y=25 b=2 o=15 i=9 2. Add all of the numbers together to create a kind of super number. 62 3. Add the digits of the number together. 8 4. Find the post of this number (step 2) in your LJ. If you don't have that many posts, add the digits together again. 62nd post 5. Take the digit you noted in step 3, and count that many words into the post. "LSD" 6. Use the resulting word in a google image search, and select a picture from the first page and post the results.
The LSD hot dog! woo!!!!

So here I am, at work again, contemplating what to write.... Nothing exciting goes on anymore, and I doubt it ever will. I spent most the weekend at Llama's due to the Hurricany goodness of the time. The entire complex was flooded all weekend so I couldn't go home until about 4:00pm yesterday. It was devestating me because there was like no food at her house, but there was at my house. :-( Oh well.... 
So, three weeks till my trip to maine and new york. Kevin is flying me up there for his birthday for the weekend. I plan to have fun, as much as I can anyway.... I'm scared about it. I'm scared that maybe my feelings for him aren't what they used to be and maybe his are. I'm scared that if I go up there and spend this great weekend with him, that I won't wanna go home. I'm scared that I may want to, but he won't.... And I'm scared to hurt him if my feelings aren't the same... I dunno... But I still want to go to see him and spend time with him because we never got to do that here.... It got so intense so fast that I got scared and pulled away. I just... don't want this to be a bad experience and I don't want it to end wrong.... 
I don't know.... I don't know what I'm doing anymore. Everything is so different anymore.... Llama and I looked through our high school yearbook this weekend.... That was uber depressing. Everytime I flipped a page there was another person I was friends with. I actually stopped and counted it out, and I basically had over 400 people that I was friends with or social with my senior year of high school. And I look at my life now... I have Llama and Panda, sometimes. Other than that, nada. I don't like that... I don't like that if I fight with Llama I'm screwed and stuck at home. Life sucks. Oh well... I'm gonna get back to work now, so, maybe I'll try and write more later. Peace kids.
Jay.

Just kinda here still... never have anything great to write in here.... Boring life... boring times.... I helped Llama move in to her apartment this weekend... omg that was shitty! I hate manual labor! Not that I did any or anything... 
And PANDA! I tried to call you for your birthday but no homo. haha, get it? get it? 
Anyways... I'm at work... I'm growing a beard. I thought I would try and rock the manly look for a few.... Who knows if it'll take... 
I'm going tanning after work today. I haven't gone since last friday. I feel so white. White is no good. I have to look like some kind of minority besides the gay thing.... heh
Anyways, I'm gonna get headin off.. maybe I'll find something interesting to write later.... 
VAGINA!

Jay.

So life is boring, nothing new going on. Trying to bust my butt to pay off everything and get my life in order. Trying to get a new car.... It looks like the goal keeps getting further and further away from me..... Everytime I think I have something under control, something happens and it all goes to shit and I have to start all over again. Oh well. 
Work sucks anymore... I'm not happy with my job. I find myself going home most days and keeping to myself. I tend to just wanna be home and do not much of anything else... On some occassions I go out with Jesse, but not really that often anymore and that's about it.... I just... don't want much else right now. I just wanna be by myself completely. I'm not ready for all the complications of it all... 
I have completely given up on dating. I figure it's just not for me anymore... like Buffy said.... 
"I figured there was always something wrong with me, because I couldn't make it work... but maybe I'm not supposed to." -Buffy
"Because you're the slayer?" -Angel
"No... Because... ok, I'm cookie dough."-Buffy, angel gives her a strange look. "I'm not done baking. I'm not finished becoming... whoever the hell it is I'm gonna be. And I keep thinking... If I get through this thing, and the next, and, the next... maybe one day I turn around and I'm ready. I'm cookies. And if someone wanted to eat m... enjoy, warm delicious cookie me... then that's fine. That'll be then. When I'm ready."-Buffy.

There once was a girl from nan-tucket... who came and sat on a bucket... she didn't wear a sheet, and now she has dirty feet, with two little babies running a mucket. 

So yeah, poor poor panda... all pregnant and stuff.... I told her barebacking was only for the pros.... Well, I hope the abortion goes well.... And I hope you feel better soon. Love and kisses to my poor pregnant barefooted naked-no-sheet-havin bitch, Panda. MUAH! 

Kiss noises,
Teddy.

So, I give up completely. 
I give up on boys.
I give up on friends.
I give up on social lives. 
I give up on sleeping. 
I give up on leaving the house.
well... maybe for work.
I'm gonna throw my ass head first into work and nothing else... I'm getting a part time job that will suck up all my free time so I can save mad money for a new car. 
I don't have much else to do... 
I had a wicked bad conversation with Joey last night... He wasn't so much the bad part, just... the emotion outlet part was bad... pretty much left me to conclude I give up. 
I apparently fucked that boy up a thousand times worse than I thought. 
And not just him, it seems. 
I've been getting assaulted by my ex's randomly for a few weeks now and they all agree that I'm a severe ass. 
So, like I said, I give up. I've been without dating or sex or any of the above since February now. 
Blah.
That's like world record for me. 
So yeah... I just give up.... I can't even be a good friend well. I'm an ass to all of them . 
I'm just an ass period. 
So, I give up. I'm not meant to have friends or reltionships or anything at all. I'm meant to be old bitter and alone. 
I think it's a look I could rock so hard.... 
oh well... goin to bed. Later peoples.... 
Jay.

So yeah... no Jeff yesterday. I tried calling him a few times and there was no answer.... and his machine is all full, too. So... oh well. 
I fell asleep early yesterday. I was just mad tired.... Sorry Panda.... didn't mean to shirk you.... hehe, shirk.... I like that word. lol 
Anyways... so now I'm at work, all tired and stuff.... I wanna go home and curl up in bed.... hehe
I've been very antisocial lately and I don't know why... like, it's been almost a month now... The only person I stand being around is panda(catina) and anyone else just makes me grumpy... lol 
I don't know what my problem is.... Maybe it's because I've been around the same people too long... my friends usually change every six months.... I get bored with people and then make new friends... oh well.... 
gotta get back to work. later all!
Jay.

So... last night... Jessie came by to annoy and harrass me like usual, and we got into this talk about relationships and such.... We talked about how she's bored with it all and blah blah blah... and I talked about how I'm completely done with it. My exact response was something like, "I don't need sex or a boyfriend, or anything. All I need is to masturbate several times a day and to play the sims, and I'll be set." And she had quite the little giggle fest over that.... and so then she jinxed me hardcore.... "Just when you have given up and aren't really looking anymore, that's when it'll find you."
So what happens? I go back inside to sit at my computer on gay.com, marveling the studpidity of everyone else in there... and then in pops Jeff. 
Jeff... the only guy that I ever regret anything about... the only guy I was crazy in love with, but never had the chance to do anything about it.... 
Yeah, him. Catina knows who I'm talkin about.... 
Anyways, so in he comes and I'm just sitting there, going "oh fuck! Oh fuck! Oh fuck!" to myself.... and eventually, I get up the nerve to talk to him.... 
The last time we talked, he got VERY angry with me and stormed off and we haven't said a word to each other since. 
So I messaged him and was like, "I know you probably won't respond to this, and that's ok, but I still wanted to say hi to you and let you know I still worry about you...." 
And then he replied.... and I was shocked as hell... We made boring chit chat for a few, the basic, how ya been, whatcha been up to, blah blah blah.
Then out of nowhere.....
"I miss you."
I didn't know what to say to that and it just grew from there.... 
So, in the meantime.... we're starting over with each other and taking it slow. I'm gonna call him today after work.... 
I don't even know what to say to him right now... I was madly in love with this kid... but I wasn't ready for him before, so I fucked up.... And I doubt I'm really ready now, but... I'm not gonna let myself fuck up again, dammit. 
Oh well... on other fronts, six days now. 21 is just round the corner... and my brother is starting on my car today.... 
I told Jessie last night that I'm not driving for my birthday, since I plan to be trashed out of my mind... and she won't drive her car out there. She was like, I'll drive your car, but I'm not taking mine out there. I was like, fuck no. I'm not having my car out there either because if I get drunk.... I will be a fucking asshole about someone driving my car. I don't let ANYONE drive my car. I let Jessie drive when it was my mom's car, I didn't care. But it's MINE now, in my name, my insurance, my headache. No one fuckin drives it but me, and if they do, they're damn lucky(CATINA). =P
So yeah.... Who knows... I was like, I'm not driving, my car is not going out there, and if no one else is driving me for my BIRTHDAY, then I won't go. Period. I WILL get beyond plastered for my birthday and I will NOT drive my car, or have my car within my access when that happens. So, if it won't be at the bar, I have no problem drinking at home. =) 
Oh well... I'm headin out to do work now. Later kids.
Jay.

blah... long boring weekend... Not much else to say to that fact. My brother has my car for the next two weeks to fix it up and paint it for me. It's in great shape, but just needs some work... needs some dents fixed and some brakework.... So, he's doing all of that schmidt this week and then next week I have vacation. YAY! 
Ok, not much else to say....
7 days till I'm 21! wooo!!!! 
Ok, later guys.
Jay.

So, ok, here's some little survey thing Heidi came up with, and I am answering it just for her. Hope you're happy. =P

((Could I date? yeah definitely. Could I sleep with? Probably. It's just a nut. I don't like em anyways. ))

((Oh, it needs work. lol It's not big or anything... just needs work to be more... plump. lol ))

On an open book
On a grand piano
On a DVD player 

Duh, an open book((I second that one.))

what size party would you prefer to attend?  ((A BIG party where I don't have to talk to people I don't like if I don't want to. =)))

Do you think that smarter people are capeable of deeper love? ((no. I think smarter people are capable of closing off until they completely fall head over heels in love and let someone in. The more naive people fall in love at the drop of a hat. HI! ::waves::))

Do you plan to have kids? ((hell no! Kids are fine, as long as you can give em back. I'm too selfish for children. Me me me me me!!!))

Have you ever broken up with a girlfriend/boyfriend because they did not want to have children? ((No... but I broke up with a boyfriend because he didn't tell me he had children. Five, to be exact. =)))

Would you let your kids watch as much t.v. as they wanted, as long as they said their homework was done? ((No. I'd make em play outside. A LOT. An outdoors kid is usually not a lazy slobby kid. =)))

Would you wait for someone you loved, who was framed and wrongly put into jail for 14 years? ((No... I'd go run someone over by "accident" and plea out for it as long as I could end up in the same place as him. hehe))

Are you going to run away as soon as it is commitment time? ((Ever seen runaway bride? That's me. ))

((It depends... On what my financial situation was. If I could afford the loss without destroying myself, I would. If the friend was good enough and someone I cared enough for. ))


If someone you barely knew asked you how many people you'd had sex with, would you answer? ((I would be an ass and tell them 54 donkies. haha, get it? ass? donkies? Come on! It was funny!!))

Could you date a person who had a large imperfection (ex: mole, birthmark, etc.)? ((as long as it wasn't like detrimental to certain acts we'd be performing.... lol ))

Yes, I believe so
No, not yet / temporarily sidetracked
I already have that job
I don't plan to work in ten years 
((I won't be working in ten years. My rich husband will take care of it all. lol ))

Are you modest? ((not even a little bit. lol))

((rock star. Yay crazy sex!))

((I improvise))

((not for the most part. But throughout the course of the relationship, at some times they are))

Would you rather find "the one" the first time you date someone, or after many attempts? (many attempts)((2nd))

If you accidently hit a parked car while driving, would you leave a note with your contact information? ((Hell no! I'd stop, remove all the ecidence and make sure there were no witnesses, killing if I had to, and then get the hell out of there, dumping my car and buying a new one. =)))

If you don't do anything at all for an entire day, how does that make you feel? good or bad? ((Good the first day. Trashy the second day. lol))

Do you feel Art has heavily influenced who you are? ((Yes. A lot about my personality I've picked up from shows I loved with characters I grew to love. I.E. Buffy... I could totally write the scripts myself just based off my personality. lol ))



-----------------
So, there's the end. I would just like to state for the record that I HATE surveys and if you've read this far.... 

Poor poor child.....

So my weekend was long and interesting... lol 
Friday, after work, Catina and I went and worked out, which was way faboo... Then we went and got pretty and went out to Chambers. John was supposed to go with his friend Patrick, and apparently did, but forgot his phone, so, couldn't call me and we never saw each other.... It was like ex boyfriend night again. I saw a few of them. Avoided them all well. lol 

Me and Catina went, and her friend whose name I suddenly cannot remember.... We were there for a while and had a good time.... danced like mofo's, people watched, drooled over the strippers..... Then headed out. We went to take her friend home and oh my god.... I live in st pete. Her friend lives in Shore Acres. Not really that far from me. BUT, this chick lives in like BFE shore acres.... I'm talking like all the way back, four rights and seven lefts three bridges and a lake down there. lol So, getting there, not bad at all. Leaving.... I attempted to do it on my own. So, Catina laid down to nap because she was tired.... 
OH
MY
GOD....

So at work, Brian brought in the book that like, tells you all about yourself based on your birthday. Just like a hooscope thing, but based on the actual day you were born. It was really interesting and VERY true about me.... here ya go, enjoy.


***** June Twenty-Eighth*****

The Day of Emotional Stimulation

Those born on June 28th generally put emotion before reason, and their approach to matters is direct and immediate. They make a most universal appeal to their co-workers, friends or family, a large part of which is the humor and cajoling they employ. Since humor is a superior way to reach peeople, they usually succeed in making an impression.
June 28 people have a way of moving others to react to them emotionally, and may in fact be deliberately provocative when trying to garner attention. The shock value they elicit is considerable and those who know them sooner or later come to expect almost anything. Although they may appear highly spontaneous due to their antics, most of what they do is well thought out beforehand. Indedd, those born on this day are masters at anticipating the effect they will produce.
Generally June 28 people eschew patient, subtle persuasion in favor of an all-out frontal attack. Yet, they are so proficient at what they do and so masterful in their detailed planning, that they rarely misjudge their audience or target group. Those born on this day tend to be more extroverted than introverted, but nontheless are deep, complex individuals who are not easily understood.
Many June 28 people are leaders and movers in their family circle or social group. As employees they can tuck themselves away for a time in a quiet place and work unnassumingly but if they sense an opportunity to share a funny story or make and outrageous comment they will tend to go for it. Logical thinking is not their forte, however, and it is more often their consistent work ethic or inspiration that makes them good employees. But for those born on this day, diligence at work does not neccissarily mean order at home, and personal areas of their life(love, housework, raising children, keeping appointments, etc.) may be quite chaotic, even completely out of hand. 
Probably the worst punishment for June 28 people is to go unappreciated or ignored. Some born on this day gyrate back and forth between an intensely social need for interaction and appreciation on the one hand and the urge to be alone with their eccentricities on the other. Mates and children of such June 28 people must either have a great sense of humor and loads of tolerance or perhaps blind love to put up with them.
Those born on June 28 often display a great objective interest in people. Because they are fascinated with human characteristics(particularly those of children), they may become taken by studies of behavior, history, language or anthropology. In this respect they can make excellent psychologists who offer insight into people's motivations, thoughts and actions. In their circle they are often consulted where a matter of human nature is concerned but may not be taken seriously by everyone due to their habit of putting people on. Behind the jovial facade, however, a June 28 person is most often hypersensitive and serious. 

Numbers and Planets

Those born on the 28th of the month are ruled by the number 1(2+8=10, 1+0=1), and by the sun. Those ruled by the number 1 are highly individual, of a definite viewpoint and eager to rise to the top. Because June 28 people are, as mentioned, strongly dominant types, they must beware of being driven by their power urges or drowning others out in a flood of emotion(emphasized by the influence of the moon, Cancer's ruler). The Sun carries in its symbolism strong creative energy and fire, which should be kept floing steadily rather than allowed to sporadically flare out of control.

Tarot

The 1st card of the Major Arcana is The Magician, who symbolizes intellect, communication, information, as well as magic. Over his head is an infinity symbol, which in some Tarot decks takes the form of a hat, in other a halo. Many interpretations may be drawn, one of which is that the Magician recognizes the cyclical and unending nature of life and is empowered by this understanding. The positive traits suggested by this first card include diplomatic skill and shrewdness but, negatively, lack of scruples and opportunism. The choice rests with June 28th people whether to use their charismatic qualities for moral or immoral ends. 

Health(my favorite section)

June 28 people truly like to eat and often suffer problems with their weight. Thei flamboyant nature can lead them to think of meals as events, focusing on the delight of the meal and the company rather than the nutritional content. This can create all sorts of digestice problems, including those of the stomach, liver, gall bladder and intestines. Those born on this day have a higher than normal incidence of addiction and would be better off avoiding experimentation with chemical sunstances. Liver problems here tend to accompany excess alcohol consumption. Regular physical exercise of a vigorous sort is recommended for June 28 people who too often exercise in bed and leave it at that.

Advice

Being the center of attention is fun, but we all have to grow up sooner or later. Work on your destructive side. Find a way to hold your tongue when necessary, while maintaining your fine sense of humor.



That's it folks. If you read all that, then you are JUST as bored as I was to be writing it all. lol But yeah, so that's me. It's a perfect description.... Scary as hell, but right on. I'm gonna go run to find some of my friend's descriptions. Later all. =)
Jay.
